    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chlorinated copper phthalocyanine pigment that was commercially introduced in 1938 by DuPont. Monastral green is made from the same phthalocyanine base as Monastral blue but is modified by chlorination.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
